## Mathematical models

Mixture effects were evaluated using two different models, i.e., the theoretical additivity (TA) and the concentration addition (CA) (Foucquier and Guedj  2015 ; Cedergreen et al.  2008 ). The TA model calculates the mixture effect by simple summation of individual effects from each single compound in the mixture. This model was used as described by Weber et al. ( 2005 ): \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
